parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when the vehicle loses power while driving on a highway or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while idling or in motion
the engine shuts off without warning
the power steering and brakes are lost
and the engine jumps under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when the vehicle loses power or stalls while driving on a highway or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the transmission has to bear down going up a hill
transmission fluid leaks around the main seal
and the vehicle has extended shifts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and coolant leakage, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: causing the crankcase coolant to become contaminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mount failure can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: and the engine jumps under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system failure can cause carbon monoxide poisoning, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: and carbon monoxide fumes enter the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe mounts can cause the engine to drop, leading to loss of steering control, accidents, and potential injuries.
The failure of the rear motor mounts can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: movement in the engine and transmission

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front body mounts can cause the door to come loose and open while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Door comes loose and opens while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe bolts can cause the steering to fail, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: vehicle comes to a complete stop without brakes being applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering to become stiff or lock up, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering becomes stiff or locks up

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rods can cause the steering to become unstable, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the steering column or rack and pinion can cause the steering to become stiff or lock up, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering becomes stiff or locks up

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mounts can cause the power steering to fail, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
